# Real-Time Chat & Group Chat Implementation

Adding DM and group chat functionality using Socket.io for real-time messaging.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] `src/models/conversation.model.js`
- `type`: enum `dm`, `group`
- `participants`: Array of ObjectId refs to users
- `name`: String (for group chats)
- `admin`: ObjectId ref (group creator)
- `lastMessage`: ObjectId ref to message
- `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `src/models/message.model.js`
- `conversation`: ObjectId ref
- `sender`: ObjectId ref to user
- `text`: String
- `readBy`: Array of ObjectId refs
- `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `src/controllers/chat.controller.js`
- `getConversations` — list all conversations for current user
- `getOrCreateDM` — find existing DM or create new one
- `createGroup` — create a group chat with participants
- `getMessages` — get paginated messages for a conversation
- `sendMessage` — send a message (also emits via Socket.io)
- `addGroupMember` / `removeGroupMember`

#### [NEW] `src/routes/chat.routes.js`
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/chat` | List conversations |
| POST | `/api/chat/dm/:userId` | Get/create DM |
| POST | `/api/chat/group` | Create group |
| GET | `/api/chat/:id/messages` | Get messages |
| POST | `/api/chat/:id/messages` | Send message |
| PUT | `/api/chat/:id/members` | Add member |
| DELETE | `/api/chat/:id/members/:userId` | Remove member |

#### [MODIFY] `server.js`
- Add Socket.io server alongside Express
- Handle `connection`, `join-conversation`, `send-message`, `typing` events

#### [MODIFY] `src/app.js`
- Wire `/api/chat` routes

